{% extends "./_style-guide-layout.njk" %}
{% set title = "Typography" %}

{% block main %}

	<h1>Typography</h1>

	<nav>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="#intro">Intro</a></li>
			<li><a href="#headings">Headings</a></li>
			<li><a href="#paragraphs">Paragraphs</a></li>
			<li><a href="#links">Links</a></li>
			<li><a href="#lists">Lists</a></li>
			<li><a href="#quotations">Quotations</a></li>
		</ul>
	</nav>

	<section id="intro">
		<h2>Intro</h2>

		<ul>
			<li>Use semantic typographic elements</li>
			<li>Use a semantic typographic structure and hierarchy</li>
		</ul>

		{% example -%}
			<h1>Heading 1</h1>
			<h2>Heading 2</h2>
			<p>Lorem <strong>ipsum</strong> dolor sit amet, <em>consectetur</em> adipiscing elit. Proin pretium, tortor non rhoncus rhoncus 12<sup>th</sup>, libero turpis varius felis, sit amet rutrum massa dolor id velit. Etiam dignissim lacus <a href="#">vitae lacinia</a> vulputate.</p>
			<h3>Heading 3</h3>
			<p>Here is a list of some things:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>The first thing</li>
				<li>And another</li>
				<li>Last thing</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>And an ordered list of things</h2>
			<ol>
				<li>The first thing</li>
				<li>And another</li>
				<li>Last thing</li>
			</ol>
		{%- endexample %}
	</section>

	<section id="headings">
		<h2>Headings</h2>

		<ul>
			<li>use Lato Light (200)</li>
			<li>use sentence case for headings</li>
			<li>use headings consistently to create a clear hierarchy</li>
		</ul>

		{% example -%}
			<h1>Heading 1</h1>
			<h2>Heading 2</h2>
			<h3>Heading 3</h3>
			<h4>Heading 4</h4>
			<h5>Heading 5</h5>
			<h6>Heading 6</h6>
		{%- endexample %}
	</section>

	<section id="paragraphs">
		<h2>Paragraphs</h2>

		<ul>
			<li>use <code>class="lead"</code> for leading, important paragraphs</li>
			<li>stick to 10 words per line as a guide</li>
		</ul>

		{% example -%}
			<p class="lead">
				Curabitur dapibus risus at sem fermentum rhoncus sit amet vitae lectus. Morbi molestie, tortor et ultrices eleifend, nisi velit suscipit sem, et pulvinar nunc sapien sit amet risus. Donec pretium consequat mauris, quis ullamcorper massa pretium nec. Etiam porta arcu nunc, vel pharetra velit elementum at.
			</p>
			<p>
				Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. In nibh augue, pulvinar nec condimentum in, vulputate a ipsum. Nulla facilisi. Sed et ex id nulla consequat bibendum nec quis nisi. Sed fermentum nisi nec velit finibus luctus. Ut felis turpis, facilisis quis leo vitae, porta mattis urna. Pellentesque at sollicitudin justo.
			</p>
			<p>
				Donec tincidunt pretium mi, sit amet mattis leo auctor quis. In hac habitasse platea dictumst. Maecenas condimentum fringilla arcu eu convallis. Maecenas varius, orci ut fringilla varius, nibh felis sodales nunc, id ornare urna ex et urna. Donec commodo vestibulum bibendum. Donec in odio erat. Proin dapibus fermentum arcu, et volutpat ligula ultrices viverra.
			</p>
		{%- endexample %}
	</section>

	<section id="links">

		<h2>Links</h2>

		<ul>
			<li>Use <code>rel="external"</code> for external links</li>
		</ul>

		{% example -%}
			<p><a href="#">A link on its own</a></p>
			<p>This is some text with <a href="#">a link inside it</a>.</p>
		{%- endexample %}

	</section>

	<section id="lists">

		<h2>Lists</h2>

		<h3>Default lists</h3>

		{% example -%}
			<p>Here is a list:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Item 1</li>
				<li>Item 2</li>
				<li><a href="#">Item 3</a></li>
			</ul>
		{%- endexample %}

		<h3>Featured lists</h3>

		<ul>
			<li>Use featured lists when you want more impact</li>
			<li>Try to stick to a maximum of 4 items in a featured list</li>
		</ul>

		{% example -%}
			<p>Here is a featured list:</p>
			<ul class="list list--featured">
				<li>Item 1</li>
				<li>Item 2</li>
				<li>Item 3</li>
			</ul>
		{%- endexample %}

	</section>

	<section id="quotations">
		<h2>Quotations</h2>

		<ul>
			<li>use a citation where possible</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>Simple block quotation</h3>

		{% example "html" -%}
			<blockquote class="quote">
				<p>In 2015, 74% of staff rated NICE as a good place to work.</p>
			</blockquote>
		{%- endexample %}

		<h3>Block quotation w/ citation</h3>

		{% example "html" -%}
			<blockquote class="quote">
				<p>Older people using home care services have a home care plan that identifies how their personal priorities and outcomes will be met.</p>
				<footer>
					- <cite><a href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/qs123">Home care for older people, NICE quality standard</a></cite>
				</footer>
			</blockquote>
		{%- endexample %}

		<h3>Block quotation w/ citation</h3>

		{% example "html" -%}
			<blockquote class="quote">
				<p>We do the right work in the right way at NICE. We mix content, dev, design and research at the start to solve user problems.  We produce things quickly, get data and refine. </p>
				<footer>
					<cite><strong>Dafydd</strong> - Content Team</cite>
				</footer>
			</blockquote>
		{%- endexample %}

		<h3>Quotation within a grid</h3>

		<p>Quotations can be nested within grids, for example alongside an image:</p>

		{% example "html" -%}
			<div class="grid">
				<div class="grid__item one-whole tablet--one-half">
					<img src="//placehold.it/640x360" alt="A placeholder" />
				</div>
				<div class="grid__item one-whole tablet--one-half">
					<blockquote class="quote">
						<p>This is a quotation inside a grid</p>
						<footer>
							- <cite>With a source</cite>
						</footer>
					</blockquote>
				</div>
			</div>
		{%- endexample %}

	</section>

{% endblock %}
